<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-09-03T12:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-09-03T12:44:00-05:00" n="552" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d552">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.515/75: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Hibbard</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-09-03T17:00:00-00:44">September
                                    3, 1942—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received September 4—8:41 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>287. Department’s telegram no. 211, August 29, 9 [<hi rend="italic">4</hi>] p.m. I have received today a note from the Liberian
                            Secretary of State confirming the agreement for acquisition of British
                            current coin in Liberia in exchange for United States current coin as
                            contained in the Department’s telegram No. 187, August 3, 8 p.m. The
                            note is the same as the previous one except that paragraph 3 has been
                            omitted at my request in accordance with the Treasury’s wishes. See my
                            despatch no. 779 of August 29 [<hi rend="italic">25</hi>].<note n="75" xml:id="d552fn75">Not printed.</note>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hibbard</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>